text: Zakerana mysorensis (Mysore frog) is a species of frog that is endemic to the Western Ghats, India. It is only known from its type locality, Jog in Shimoga district, Karnataka state. ==References== mysorensis Category:Frogs of India Category:Endemic fauna of the Western Ghats Category:Taxa named by C. R. Narayan Rao Category:Amphibians described in 1922
